WEBVTT

00:01.101 --> 00:02.101
("spring" by angel olsen plays)

00:02.103 --> 00:06.304
♪♪♪

00:06.306 --> 00:09.575
♪ don't take it for granted ♪

00:09.710 --> 00:12.177
♪ love when you have it ♪

00:12.179 --> 00:15.247
♪ you might be looking over ♪

00:15.316 --> 00:18.183
♪ a lonelier shoulder ♪

00:18.185 --> 00:19.785
(breathing hard)

00:19.920 --> 00:21.386
<i> Liam: "dear jenny,</i>

00:21.389 --> 00:23.455
<i> I'm in a rehab for vets.</i>

00:23.590 --> 00:26.658
<i> I think about you a lot,</i>

00:26.660 --> 00:28.860
<i> And I think about how I left."</i>

00:28.995 --> 00:30.762
♪ now that we're older ♪

00:33.000 --> 00:35.267
<i> Liam: "I know I promised</i>
<i> not to leave you."</i>

00:35.269 --> 00:37.335
♪ little we know... ♪

00:37.405 --> 00:39.538
<i> Liam: "I'm sorry it took</i>
<i> so many months.</i>

00:39.607 --> 00:41.540
<i> I was pretty messed up</i>
<i> for a while."</i>

00:41.609 --> 00:44.142
♪ I should have noticed ♪

00:44.211 --> 00:46.678
<i> Liam: "but I'm in a good place</i>
<i> right now..."</i>

00:48.049 --> 00:50.515
♪ won't ever leave ♪

00:51.819 --> 00:52.951
<i> "and I miss you."</i>

00:54.555 --> 00:56.688
♪ one to deceive ♪

00:56.690 --> 01:00.292
♪ I'm beginning to wonder ♪

01:00.361 --> 01:03.295
♪ if anything's real ♪

01:03.364 --> 01:07.366
♪ guess we're just
at the mercy ♪

01:07.368 --> 01:10.102
♪ of the way that we feel ♪

01:10.171 --> 01:17.176
♪♪♪

01:17.178 --> 01:20.445
(bicycle rattles along)

01:21.916 --> 01:28.921
♪♪♪

01:28.923 --> 01:30.989
♪♪♪

01:30.991 --> 01:32.724
(doorknob rattles)

01:32.793 --> 01:36.027
♪♪♪

01:36.063 --> 01:38.930
♪ alive with a past ♪

01:38.966 --> 01:42.066
♪ no other can share ♪

01:42.103 --> 01:45.303
♪ alone with a heart ♪

01:45.305 --> 01:48.406
♪ no other can bear ♪

01:48.442 --> 01:51.743
♪ so give me some heaven ♪

01:51.812 --> 01:53.412
<i> Liam: "I'd like to see you.</i>

01:53.547 --> 01:55.948
<i> Let me know if you feel</i>
<i> the same.</i>

01:55.950 --> 01:57.149
<i> Je t'embrasse."</i>

01:57.284 --> 01:59.851
♪ make me eternal ♪

01:59.854 --> 02:03.421
♪ there in your smile ♪

02:03.457 --> 02:09.628
♪♪♪

02:09.630 --> 02:12.597
(music turns discordant)

02:14.902 --> 02:17.402
(bike clatters,
running footsteps)

02:19.540 --> 02:21.339
- Shirley?

02:24.311 --> 02:25.911
Are you okay?

02:30.151 --> 02:32.217
(birds chirp)

02:33.854 --> 02:35.721
<i> (shocked breath)</i>

02:37.024 --> 02:38.523
♪♪♪

02:43.998 --> 02:45.997
<i> Neil: With everything</i>
<i> that's happened,</i>

02:46.033 --> 02:47.399
<i> Do you wanna see liam?</i>

02:47.401 --> 02:49.334
(traffic whooshes by)

02:49.336 --> 02:50.902
- I mean, yea--

02:50.905 --> 02:54.005
Yeah, I mean,
of course I do. I just...

02:54.041 --> 02:55.139
The last time we saw each other,

02:55.176 --> 02:56.808
We said, you know,
he said, "I love you,"

02:56.877 --> 03:00.212
He said he was sorry,

03:00.347 --> 03:02.280
And then we said goodbye.

03:02.349 --> 03:04.349
- And you thought goodbye
was permanent.

03:04.351 --> 03:06.418
- Yeah, I mean, I didn't hear
from him for five months.

03:06.487 --> 03:08.286
I mean, what was I supposed
to think?

03:08.355 --> 03:10.355
- Well, there's no statutory
limit on love.

03:10.357 --> 03:13.592
<i> - Yeah, but I don't understand</i>
<i> how, in my gut, I was so sure,</i>

03:13.594 --> 03:17.262
And yet I was so wrong,
you know?

03:18.465 --> 03:21.032
- Gut feelings are conditioned
responses...

03:21.068 --> 03:23.302
Sometimes to trauma.

03:23.304 --> 03:25.837
In your personal life,

03:25.973 --> 03:28.039
<i> Are there other people</i>
<i> who've left?</i>

03:29.643 --> 03:32.444
- Well, I mean, my sister died.

03:32.513 --> 03:35.447
That's leaving, I guess.

03:35.516 --> 03:37.749
- And then your mother left,
jenny.

03:41.655 --> 03:43.621
<i> Does thinking about it</i>
<i> shut you down?</i>

03:45.392 --> 03:48.126
- No... No.

03:48.128 --> 03:50.695
<i> - It's perfectly natural to go</i>
<i> to a place of "no,"</i>

03:50.764 --> 03:53.064
In your body and your mind,

03:53.133 --> 03:55.166
To protect yourself.

03:56.670 --> 03:58.136
<i> Here's some homework:</i>

03:58.138 --> 03:59.871
For the rest of the week,
I want you to say yes

03:59.940 --> 04:01.440
To everything.
- (laughs)

04:01.442 --> 04:03.441
<i>- No matter what your gut says.</i>
<i> - (laugh dies out)</i>

04:04.745 --> 04:07.946
<i> Let your life unfold, jenny.</i>

04:07.948 --> 04:09.547
<i> Surprise yourself.</i>

04:13.954 --> 04:15.086
(traffic whooshes by)

04:15.122 --> 04:16.955
(phone rings)

04:18.558 --> 04:20.559
- (chuckles nervously)
it's work.

04:20.694 --> 04:22.127
<i> Dr. Cheng: Always on call.</i>

04:22.129 --> 04:23.595
I can relate.

04:24.698 --> 04:26.231
<i> So your biopsy shows that</i>

04:26.233 --> 04:29.634
<i> You have solitary spinal</i>
<i> plasmacytoma.</i>

04:29.703 --> 04:31.370
- Uh...

04:31.505 --> 04:33.971
- A low tumour in
the lumbar spine.

04:35.142 --> 04:40.645
♪♪♪

04:40.681 --> 04:42.781
Your lumbar puncture confirms
that it hasn't spread,

04:42.850 --> 04:44.249
Which is good.

04:44.251 --> 04:45.750
- Okay.

04:47.054 --> 04:48.586
<i> - The tumour explains the pain</i>
<i> in your leg,</i>

04:48.622 --> 04:51.122
<i> And why it progressed</i>
<i> to your back.</i>

04:51.158 --> 04:52.790
- Okay.

04:52.826 --> 04:54.258
<i> - Without the pain,</i>

04:54.295 --> 04:56.595
<i> We wouldn't have caught it</i>
<i> as quickly as we did.</i>

04:56.597 --> 04:59.798
<i> So, that's a good thing too.</i>
- Mm-hmm.

04:59.867 --> 05:02.000
- You'll need to start
a regular course of radiation

05:02.002 --> 05:03.535
As soon as possible.

05:03.604 --> 05:05.670
How about thursdays?

05:05.739 --> 05:07.972
- (exhales slowly) um...

05:09.043 --> 05:11.543
Uh, will I, will I be able
to work?

05:11.612 --> 05:13.612
<i> - Well, there can be some side</i>
<i> effects to the treatment -</i>

05:13.614 --> 05:15.680
<i> Fatigue, nausea -</i>

05:15.749 --> 05:17.949
<i> But you're free to work</i>
<i> if you feel up to it.</i>

05:23.357 --> 05:25.490
<i> Oh, you'll need a ride home</i>
<i> Thursday.</i>

05:25.559 --> 05:27.626
<i> We don't know how you'll react</i>
<i> to the radiation.</i>

05:27.761 --> 05:29.694
<i> You might need someone</i>
<i> to take care of you.</i>

05:32.199 --> 05:33.698
(distorted music)

05:33.701 --> 05:40.105
♪♪♪

05:40.174 --> 05:42.374
(bus rumbles,
upset woman chatters)

05:42.509 --> 05:45.377
(indistinct chatter
over police radio)

05:45.512 --> 05:49.114
(upset woman chatters, cries)

05:49.183 --> 05:50.849
Malik: Ma'am? Please, ma'am.

05:50.918 --> 05:52.917
Ma'am, stop! Stop!
You can't go there.

05:52.986 --> 05:55.387
- Suddenly, he was just there.

05:55.456 --> 05:57.756
<i> I pulled up...</i>
<i> I don't know...</i>

05:57.891 --> 05:59.691
<i> I can't get fired!</i>

05:59.693 --> 06:02.427
<i> I'm... (sobbing)</i>

06:03.731 --> 06:05.730
(indistinct police radio
chatter)

06:05.733 --> 06:09.000
(horns honk,
traffic rumbles loudly)

06:09.069 --> 06:11.202
- You're late.

06:11.271 --> 06:13.037
- Who do we have here?

06:13.107 --> 06:15.240
- Andrew park,
courier for foodscouts.

06:15.375 --> 06:17.676
He was 65.
He was hit by the van.

06:17.811 --> 06:19.544
- Mm. Cause of death, check.

06:19.546 --> 06:21.446
- Well, what you see isn't
always what you get.

06:21.582 --> 06:23.148
So we're gonna send the body
to pathology

06:23.283 --> 06:24.749
And see what they can tell us.

06:24.818 --> 06:26.551
- Death waits on no man.

06:26.553 --> 06:28.586
- Except for this woman.

06:29.656 --> 06:32.757
- (grunting in pain)

06:32.826 --> 06:35.593
(siren and traffic sounds
dampen)

06:40.134 --> 06:41.766
<i> Malik: Hey, mac.</i>

06:41.769 --> 06:44.236
Where were you?
- Minding my business.

06:44.238 --> 06:45.937
You should do the same.

06:45.939 --> 06:48.005
- Yo, are you getting some?

06:48.041 --> 06:50.308
Oh, big d, you big dog!
(laughs)

06:50.444 --> 06:51.643
- You talked to the driver?

06:51.712 --> 06:53.378
- Yeah. She said the guy came
out of nowhere,

06:53.380 --> 06:55.379
Ran right in front of her.
- Ran? He was on foot?

06:55.416 --> 06:57.215
- All the witnesses confirm
her story.

06:57.284 --> 06:59.217
- Delivery guys don't usually
travel by foot.

06:59.253 --> 07:00.785
So where's his vehicle?

07:00.854 --> 07:02.220
- Well, I'll contact
foodscouts,

07:02.289 --> 07:04.322
Ask if he used a car
or bike for deliveries.

07:04.458 --> 07:06.525
- All right.

07:06.527 --> 07:08.493
- Huh.

07:13.200 --> 07:17.068
(chimes tinkle,
birds chirp, crow caws)

07:18.605 --> 07:19.871
<i> (approaching footsteps)</i>

07:19.940 --> 07:21.473
<i> Woman: Dr. Cooper.</i>

07:23.410 --> 07:27.345
- It's beautiful here.
- Isn't it?

07:27.414 --> 07:30.882
<i> I'm sorry you're here</i>
<i> under these circumstances.</i>

07:31.017 --> 07:33.317
Normally, this is a place
of new beginnings.

07:34.822 --> 07:36.754
Right this way.

07:36.756 --> 07:38.223
(birds chirp,
chimes jingle)

07:38.358 --> 07:40.625
- So, uh, how does
the retreat work?

07:40.661 --> 07:42.227
- It's a silent retreat.

07:42.362 --> 07:45.296
Very structured schedule -
ten days, ten participants.

07:45.332 --> 07:47.098
They take workshops or seminars

07:47.234 --> 07:48.500
For about 12 hours each day.

07:49.703 --> 07:51.836
- Wow, that's a long day.

07:51.905 --> 07:53.438
- I think of it as a luxury.

07:53.440 --> 07:55.172
I mean, when's the last time
you spent

07:55.209 --> 07:58.510
All that time on nothing
but yourself?

07:58.579 --> 08:00.811
- Well, not since my son
was born.

08:01.849 --> 08:03.782
Definitely not since my dad
moved in.

08:05.652 --> 08:07.719
(crows caw, birds chirp)

08:07.854 --> 08:09.787
(blows out her breath)

08:09.789 --> 08:11.256
(footsteps crunch)

08:11.391 --> 08:13.324
- Just this way.

08:14.928 --> 08:17.996
- Did you make this maze?

08:18.065 --> 08:20.331
- It's a good metaphor
for life.

08:20.400 --> 08:21.733
(foliage rustles underfoot)

08:21.802 --> 08:23.434
- Huh.

08:26.673 --> 08:28.639
(doorknob clicks,
door creaks open)

08:31.411 --> 08:38.349
♪♪♪

08:38.418 --> 08:45.389
♪♪♪

08:47.361 --> 08:50.595
- (murmurs mantra indistinctly)

08:52.299 --> 08:54.899
(birds chirp and sing)

08:57.104 --> 08:59.871
(gloves rustle against clothes)

09:02.075 --> 09:06.210
♪♪♪

09:06.280 --> 09:08.212
(birds chirp)

09:10.917 --> 09:17.755
♪♪♪

09:19.192 --> 09:20.658
(sighs heavily)

09:20.727 --> 09:22.727
There's no sign of injury.

09:24.731 --> 09:27.599
- This is a medical form
she filled out for our records.

09:27.734 --> 09:29.801
- Shirley brownstone.

09:29.870 --> 09:32.470
No pre-existing medical
conditions,

09:32.606 --> 09:34.606
No medications.

09:34.675 --> 09:36.608
Was she exhibiting any sign
of illness?

09:36.743 --> 09:39.944
- No, nothing.
(sharp inhale)

09:40.013 --> 09:41.880
In fact, she was great.

09:42.015 --> 09:44.883
Shirley had bloomed.

09:44.885 --> 09:48.086
It's crushing that she died
here, of all places.

09:48.155 --> 09:50.421
(indistinct chatter)

09:50.490 --> 09:52.223
<i> - Why's that?</i>

09:52.225 --> 09:54.092
<i> - Because in the maze, you...</i>

09:54.161 --> 09:56.427
<i> You don't lose yourself.</i>

09:56.496 --> 09:58.295
<i> You find yourself.</i>

09:58.332 --> 10:00.564
(indistinct police radio
chatter)

10:00.601 --> 10:02.667
- I'm fareed, I'm the one
who found shirley.

10:03.770 --> 10:05.570
Can I ask, how did she die?

10:05.572 --> 10:07.038
- Uh, we don't know that yet.

10:07.173 --> 10:09.040
We're gonna have to do
an autopsy.

10:09.175 --> 10:11.042
- I can't believe that
this happened.

10:11.044 --> 10:12.576
I mean, that she died here.

10:12.613 --> 10:13.845
She just bloomed
a few days ago.

10:13.980 --> 10:16.247
- Sorry, can I, can I ask, um...

10:16.249 --> 10:18.516
What does "bloomed" mean?

10:18.518 --> 10:20.452
- Oh, it's an expression
that faye uses

10:20.454 --> 10:21.986
For a moment of transformation.

10:22.055 --> 10:24.189
When you finally break free
of whatever pain or fear

10:24.324 --> 10:25.923
Brought you here.

10:25.993 --> 10:28.459
- Hmm.

10:28.495 --> 10:30.961
Does... Does everyone
experience that?

10:32.032 --> 10:33.931
- It's what we're all working
towards.

10:33.933 --> 10:37.135
When you realize that there's
nothing standing between you

10:37.204 --> 10:39.470
And the life that you want.

10:39.506 --> 10:42.273
<i> (indistinct police radio</i>
<i> chatter)</i>

10:42.342 --> 10:44.208
- Must be nice.

10:45.612 --> 10:47.745
Therapist: (clucking tongue)
(hooves thud softly)

10:47.814 --> 10:50.348
It's okay. (smacks lips) good.

10:50.417 --> 10:52.450
(clucks tongue) come on.
(smacks lips)

10:52.585 --> 10:54.185
- Hey...
- Come on! That's it,

10:54.221 --> 10:56.020
That a girl.
(clucking tongue)

10:56.056 --> 10:58.156
Come on.
(tack jingles)

10:58.158 --> 11:00.558
How do you think she's reacting
to you today?

11:00.627 --> 11:03.594
- (softly) come here.
- Just breathe.

11:03.664 --> 11:05.096
- It's okay...

11:05.098 --> 11:07.699
(horse breathes heavily)
- keep going.

11:07.768 --> 11:09.701
- Yeah, easy...

11:11.038 --> 11:12.437
(tack jingles)

11:12.572 --> 11:13.672
(horse snorts nervously)
- it's...

11:13.807 --> 11:15.406
- Okay.
- It's okay.

11:15.442 --> 11:18.009
Establish a connection.
It's okay.

11:18.144 --> 11:20.311
- Okay, hey... Okay.

11:20.347 --> 11:21.312
(horse snorts)
- oh.

11:21.448 --> 11:23.381
- Okay.

11:23.383 --> 11:25.316
She won't settle, eh?

11:25.385 --> 11:26.785
- Just takes time.

11:26.787 --> 11:28.920
(snorts)

11:30.390 --> 11:32.990
- Hey... You and me, okay?

11:34.928 --> 11:36.660
(whispers) you and me.

11:38.799 --> 11:41.466
(horse breathes heavily)

11:41.601 --> 11:48.439
♪♪♪

11:50.243 --> 11:52.277
(smacks lips)

11:52.412 --> 11:55.613
♪♪♪

11:55.615 --> 11:58.616
(horse grunts nervously, snorts)

11:59.820 --> 12:02.487
- Maybe tomorrow, liam.
- Yeah.

12:02.622 --> 12:04.856
<i> - Just keep trying,</i>
<i> little bits at a time.</i>

12:04.925 --> 12:07.091
- Sure.
(approaching footsteps)

12:07.160 --> 12:08.626
(clears throat)

12:11.264 --> 12:14.031
- She still doesn't like you.

12:14.101 --> 12:15.767
Come on.
(clucks her tongue)

12:17.904 --> 12:21.339
- Give it time.
I'm an acquired taste.

12:24.745 --> 12:25.977
- Andrew park's cause of death

12:26.112 --> 12:28.112
Was blunt force trauma
to the head.

12:28.115 --> 12:29.981
<i> Donovan: Makes sense.</i>
<i> That van hit him pretty hard.</i>

12:30.050 --> 12:33.651
- Yeah. I found shards
of glass in his skull.

12:34.988 --> 12:36.788
I actually found something else
kind of interesting too.

12:36.923 --> 12:39.190
Once I washed off
all the blood,

12:39.325 --> 12:41.125
There were cuts like
knife marks

12:41.161 --> 12:43.060
That were not from
the accident.

12:43.096 --> 12:45.530
- Defensive wounds?
- Yeah, looks like it.

12:45.532 --> 12:47.865
<i> - Knife marks and running</i>
<i> into traffic?</i>

12:47.934 --> 12:50.034
Let me call you back.
- Okay.

12:51.471 --> 12:52.937
What's your body telling you?

12:53.006 --> 12:54.939
- Not much from the outside,

12:54.941 --> 12:57.008
But there's no external signs
of injury.

12:57.010 --> 13:00.545
She does have a rash
on her legs.

13:00.680 --> 13:02.046
<i> Poison ivy.</i>

13:02.115 --> 13:05.617
- Hmm. I have seen it
in worse places.

13:05.619 --> 13:06.818
It does make sense though.

13:06.953 --> 13:09.687
There was a lot of forest
around the retreat.

13:09.756 --> 13:12.089
- Turning tides sounds nice.

13:12.125 --> 13:14.291
- Yeah, it was uh... Peaceful.

13:14.327 --> 13:16.694
I can see how someone
would bloom there.

13:16.763 --> 13:18.262
- "bloom?"

13:19.432 --> 13:22.499
<i>Melanie: Whoa! We have a bezoar</i>
<i> in the gi tract.</i>

13:22.536 --> 13:24.102
<i> Jenny: Looks like...</i>

13:24.237 --> 13:26.571
<i> Unabsorbed pills.</i>

13:26.706 --> 13:31.175
- Takes a lot of pills
to cause a ball that size.

13:32.779 --> 13:35.046
- If shirley had "bloomed,"

13:35.181 --> 13:37.448
Then why did she take
her own life?

13:37.450 --> 13:39.717
♪♪♪

13:44.057 --> 13:45.790
K: I'm starting a pickup
<i> game with the guys</i>

13:45.792 --> 13:47.525
<i> On thursdays.</i>
<i> You wanna join?</i>

13:47.527 --> 13:50.094
<i> Donovan: Uh, I'm busy.</i>
<i> - Every Thursday?</i>

13:50.230 --> 13:52.130
I'm starting to think
you don't have a woman.

13:52.265 --> 13:53.932
You're too tense.

13:53.934 --> 13:55.600
Are you taking a class
or something?

13:55.602 --> 13:57.135
- What's the house number?
- 216.

13:57.270 --> 13:58.870
Ah, it must be something
embarrassing.

13:58.939 --> 14:00.738
Like salsa dancing
or something?

14:00.807 --> 14:02.540
- What's the guy's name?
- Randy smith.

14:02.542 --> 14:05.142
You know, I'm gonna figure
this out, right?

14:05.212 --> 14:06.810
Those hips don't lie.

14:06.847 --> 14:09.146
(laughs)

14:10.250 --> 14:12.050
(door opens)

14:12.052 --> 14:14.351
I'm detective abed,
this is detective mcavoy.

14:14.387 --> 14:15.887
Did you have food delivered
yesterday?

14:16.022 --> 14:17.755
- Yeah.

14:17.824 --> 14:19.023
- Is this the guy?

14:19.059 --> 14:20.625
- Guess so.

14:20.760 --> 14:22.093
I didn't really see him.

14:22.162 --> 14:24.728
- Was he wearing a mask?
- Yeah,

14:24.764 --> 14:26.130
But he looked asian.

14:27.467 --> 14:29.500
- Well, this guy was killed
yesterday, hit by a van.

14:29.636 --> 14:31.168
- I don't drive a van.

14:31.204 --> 14:33.104
<i> - Your house was the last</i>
<i> scheduled delivery.</i>

14:33.173 --> 14:35.239
- Oh.

14:35.242 --> 14:36.841
- There's some indication

14:36.843 --> 14:38.576
That he had an altercation
with someone.

14:38.578 --> 14:39.944
Know anything about that?

14:40.080 --> 14:42.180
- No, but that kinda thing
happens all the time now.

14:42.315 --> 14:45.282
<i> This neighbourhood's really</i>
<i> changed. Is that all?</i>

14:45.318 --> 14:47.452
- Yeah, for now.
Why don't you, uh...

14:47.454 --> 14:50.554
Give us a call if you remember
or hear anything.

14:52.025 --> 14:53.791
<i> - Uh, one more thing, um...</i>

14:53.927 --> 14:55.760
Did the delivery guy leave
on a bike?

14:55.895 --> 14:58.663
- Yeah. Took off like a bat
out of hell.

14:58.665 --> 15:00.999
Guess he had somewhere to be.

15:01.001 --> 15:03.134
(door clicks open)

15:04.471 --> 15:06.804
- He didn't really see him,
but he "looked asian?"

15:06.806 --> 15:08.573
- You know, a lot of food
delivery services

15:08.575 --> 15:11.275
Put cameras on their vehicles
for insurance purposes.

15:11.311 --> 15:12.944
- We need to find that bike.

15:14.247 --> 15:17.448
- The police did find an empty
bottle of acetaminophen

15:17.484 --> 15:19.616
<i> In your wife's room,</i>

15:19.653 --> 15:22.519
<i> So we have ruled it a suicide.</i>

15:23.623 --> 15:26.290
<i> I'm so sorry.</i>
<i> I know this hard to hear.</i>

15:26.326 --> 15:28.625
(phone rings in the distance)

15:28.662 --> 15:31.429
Had anything changed...
Recently?

15:31.498 --> 15:33.431
Like was she um...

15:33.433 --> 15:35.466
Was she sad,
or was she depressed at all?

15:37.103 --> 15:40.371
- The covid crisis was hard
on us, on everyone -

15:40.506 --> 15:43.907
Stuck at home,
nothing to do but worry -

15:43.944 --> 15:45.676
But we were fine.

15:47.313 --> 15:49.246
I thought we were fine.

15:49.282 --> 15:51.915
<i> Shirley said she was going</i>
<i> to turning tides to...</i>

15:51.952 --> 15:54.185
Re-center herself.

15:54.254 --> 15:57.588
I didn't ask specifics.

15:57.624 --> 15:59.090
<i> Three days ago,</i>
<i> she left a voicemail</i>

15:59.225 --> 16:01.658
Saying she wanted a divorce.

16:01.695 --> 16:03.761
- She didn't say why?

16:03.797 --> 16:05.730
- No.

16:05.865 --> 16:07.664
The next day...

16:07.701 --> 16:10.434
She withdrew $10,000 dollars
from our account.

16:11.671 --> 16:13.270
<i> I went there,</i>

16:13.306 --> 16:14.672
But the woman who runs
the place

16:14.741 --> 16:16.741
Wouldn't let me see her,

16:16.810 --> 16:19.744
Said "no outside contact
allowed."

16:19.813 --> 16:21.546
<i> I just wanted to talk to her.</i>

16:21.681 --> 16:23.614
<i> I would never hurt my wife.</i>

16:24.818 --> 16:25.949
(birds chirp)

16:25.986 --> 16:27.819
(chimes jingle)

16:27.821 --> 16:29.287
<i>Man: I'm here to answer phones.</i>

16:29.289 --> 16:30.688
<i> I'm not going to woo-woo</i>
<i> with you.</i>

16:30.690 --> 16:32.023
<i> Faye: Did you ever consider</i>
<i> the fact</i>

16:32.092 --> 16:33.924
<i> That you might get something</i>
<i> from the experience?</i>

16:33.960 --> 16:35.693
Man: Did you ever consider that
you're not as good at this

16:35.762 --> 16:37.694
As you think?

16:37.731 --> 16:39.597
I'm not going to do this.

16:39.732 --> 16:42.633
<i> - I am so disappointed in you,</i>
<i> oliver.</i>

16:48.441 --> 16:50.041
- You okay?

16:50.110 --> 16:53.011
- (sighs heavily)
no one in this place is okay.

16:54.247 --> 16:57.114
- Uh... I'm doctor jenny cooper,
I was uh...

16:57.183 --> 16:59.416
I was actually hoping
I could speak to faye.

16:59.452 --> 17:01.319
- She's about to start
a seminar right now.

17:01.454 --> 17:04.055
(phone rings)
uh, one second please.

17:04.190 --> 17:06.924
(phone rings)

17:06.993 --> 17:09.460
Hello? Turning tides. Yes.

17:09.595 --> 17:11.528
(meditative music plays)

17:11.564 --> 17:18.469
♪♪♪

17:18.604 --> 17:25.476
♪♪♪

17:25.611 --> 17:32.549
♪♪♪

17:32.585 --> 17:39.490
♪♪♪

17:39.625 --> 17:44.095
♪♪♪

17:44.230 --> 17:46.697
(birds chirp)

17:46.766 --> 17:49.533
- Hey, I'm looking for faye--
- shhh...

17:53.773 --> 17:56.974
Sorry, we're not allowed
to talk to anyone

17:56.976 --> 17:58.375
Outside of the workshops,

17:58.411 --> 18:01.579
And the only pleasure oliver
gets is to narc on us.

18:02.715 --> 18:04.715
- Oh...

18:04.717 --> 18:06.317
Well, he uh...

18:06.319 --> 18:08.519
He doesn't look too happy
to be here.

18:08.521 --> 18:10.121
<i> - He's faye's son.</i>

18:10.256 --> 18:13.591
He got kicked out of private
school again.

18:13.660 --> 18:15.259
You're the coroner, right?

18:17.463 --> 18:19.997
- Yeah, I'm uh...
I'm jenny cooper.

18:19.999 --> 18:21.699
- Tina.

18:21.834 --> 18:23.600
It sucks about shirley.

18:23.636 --> 18:25.536
She seemed like a nice woman.

18:25.671 --> 18:27.872
You know, the day that
she bloomed,

18:27.874 --> 18:30.174
Oh wow, was so powerful.

18:31.478 --> 18:34.077
- Yeah, I'm um... I'm trying
to make sense of her death.

18:34.114 --> 18:37.814
Because I-I don't understand
why she would kill herself

18:37.851 --> 18:41.285
If she had just bloomed,
you know?

18:42.688 --> 18:45.489
- We're not really supposed
to question faye's methods.

18:45.492 --> 18:47.925
<i> Man: What's wrong with you</i>
<i> people?!</i>

18:48.060 --> 18:49.627
<i> Can't you see this whole thing</i>
<i> is a lie?!</i>

18:49.629 --> 18:53.096
- Whoa.
- She's brainwashing you!

18:53.133 --> 18:55.432
Please, you've got to get
out of here, now,

18:55.434 --> 18:58.169
Before this place
kills you too!

18:58.304 --> 19:01.104
Why-- please!

19:01.141 --> 19:03.507
Why won't any of you listen
to me?!

19:03.576 --> 19:05.776
- Sir!
- I'm begging you, please get--

19:05.812 --> 19:07.445
- Sir!
- Listen! Listen to me!

19:07.580 --> 19:10.648
- Hey! Hey!
- You!
- Hi!

19:10.717 --> 19:12.449
I'm listening.

19:12.485 --> 19:14.618
Were you a former participant?

19:15.688 --> 19:19.056
- Um... Um, not me.
My son, jonah.

19:20.693 --> 19:22.460
(sniffs)

19:22.595 --> 19:24.995
- If you don't mind me asking,
what happened?

19:25.031 --> 19:26.296
- Uh,

19:28.034 --> 19:29.800
Um, well, before he came here,

19:29.836 --> 19:31.802
He was uh...

19:31.804 --> 19:34.805
Well, he was a little bit lost.

19:34.807 --> 19:36.240
Um...

19:37.610 --> 19:39.776
He begged us to pay for this
place - thousands of dollars.

19:42.282 --> 19:44.014
But then, when he came home,

19:47.487 --> 19:49.486
He was so much worse.

19:51.024 --> 19:53.224
- And what happened
to your son?

19:54.527 --> 19:56.593
- A month after he came here,

19:58.531 --> 20:00.864
He jumped off the humber bay
bridge.

20:03.570 --> 20:05.035
- (exhales sharply)

20:05.071 --> 20:06.637
- (sniffling)
- I'm sorry.

20:06.772 --> 20:08.872
- (sniffling)

20:10.310 --> 20:16.247
♪♪♪

20:20.520 --> 20:22.052
T crack, right?

20:22.088 --> 20:23.720
- Yeah. That's what they say.
- That's what they say.

20:23.756 --> 20:25.189
Come on.
- Here, are you ready?

20:25.191 --> 20:26.523
- Come on! Yeah, let's go. Oh!
- Oh!

20:26.593 --> 20:28.125
Oh, dad, you gotta make it
a little,

20:28.127 --> 20:29.660
You gotta make it
a little more difficult.

20:29.729 --> 20:30.928
Make it a little tougher.
- You know,

20:31.063 --> 20:32.529
Since you were a kid,
I always let you win.

20:32.565 --> 20:34.164
- Used to let me win?
Oh, that's so sweet.

20:34.234 --> 20:35.666
- But not today, baby.
- Not today?

20:35.735 --> 20:37.601
- Bring your best.
Come on, come on, come on.

20:37.737 --> 20:39.237
No, no, no!
- Oh!

20:39.372 --> 20:41.272
- I'm gonna school you!
Come on, son! Come on!

20:41.407 --> 20:43.241
Ha! Ha! Watch this, son!
- (grunts in pain)

20:43.376 --> 20:46.244
You know that's a foul, right?
- No, baby, that's game!

20:46.379 --> 20:48.145
- Ugh! You know you used
to be so much better

20:48.281 --> 20:50.414
At least hiding
how badly you cheat.

20:50.483 --> 20:52.483
- Come on now,
take your beating like a man.

20:52.552 --> 20:54.618
- (amused sigh) all right,
good game, pops.

20:54.621 --> 20:56.186
Good game.

20:58.524 --> 21:05.363
♪♪♪

21:05.498 --> 21:11.569
♪♪♪

21:11.571 --> 21:14.038
- You wanna know how an old man
like me could take you?

21:14.040 --> 21:16.774
- 'cause you cheat?
(both laugh)

21:16.776 --> 21:18.843
- Because now I'm finally
living.

21:18.978 --> 21:20.777
- And what exactly
were you doing before?

21:20.813 --> 21:23.047
- Paying bills.
Working two jobs.

21:23.049 --> 21:24.648
Waking up at the crack of dawn

21:24.717 --> 21:27.117
And coming home in the dead
of night.

21:27.153 --> 21:29.854
Now, I finally found my joy.
(chuckles)

21:29.856 --> 21:32.056
- What's her name?
- Mindy.

21:32.058 --> 21:33.657
- Oh, she's something else!
Woo!

21:33.726 --> 21:36.127
- I bet.
- You got to see her, son.

21:36.129 --> 21:38.162
She makes a good ginger beer.

21:38.297 --> 21:39.964
Oh! I need you to water
my plants.

21:39.966 --> 21:41.332
- Where're you going?

21:41.401 --> 21:43.200
- One of those all-inclusive
resorts,

21:43.336 --> 21:45.269
And all the drinks are free!

21:45.271 --> 21:47.071
- Okay, first of all,
the drinks are not free,

21:47.073 --> 21:48.672
They're included in
the thousands of dollars

21:48.741 --> 21:50.207
You pay for a vacation
like that.

21:50.276 --> 21:52.076
And second, you really think
it's a good idea

21:52.078 --> 21:53.344
To be going to a resort?

21:53.413 --> 21:55.746
- At least I'm not going
on a cruise.

21:55.881 --> 21:57.615
- Communal spaces, buffets...

21:57.750 --> 21:59.616
Dad, you're seventy.

21:59.686 --> 22:01.618
- One day it's the virus,

22:01.654 --> 22:03.220
The next day it's something
else.

22:03.356 --> 22:05.356
I'm not gonna live in
that fear, son.

22:05.425 --> 22:07.892
I spent my whole life waiting
to shine.

22:08.027 --> 22:10.561
- Yeah, whatever.
(phone rings)

22:10.563 --> 22:12.096
What, malik?

22:14.700 --> 22:16.367
- You gotta go back to work?
- Yeah.

22:16.502 --> 22:18.769
Just check if you can get
a refund on that cruise,

22:18.904 --> 22:21.972
All right?
- It's not a cruise!

22:24.310 --> 22:27.711
- Shirley was the second person
to commit suicide here.

22:29.182 --> 22:31.115
- Did you know the success
rate of alcoholics anonymous

22:31.184 --> 22:32.516
Is five to ten percent?

22:32.585 --> 22:35.185
Meanwhile, turning tides's
success rate is 85 percent.

22:36.522 --> 22:39.457
- Okay. But I'm still gonna
have to question your methods.

22:39.459 --> 22:41.258
- I know my methods
can't save everyone,

22:41.327 --> 22:42.860
But I won't turn anyone away,

22:42.929 --> 22:45.196
Not even the lost causes.

22:45.198 --> 22:47.931
- So shirley and jonah
were lost causes?

22:48.000 --> 22:50.801
- Most people leave here
transformed for the better.

22:50.870 --> 22:53.336
- At what cost? Because
shirley's husband said

22:53.373 --> 22:56.140
That she took out $10,000
dollars before she died

22:56.209 --> 22:58.142
And he came here to talk
to her about it,

22:58.144 --> 22:59.743
But you wouldn't let him in.

22:59.779 --> 23:01.344
- Beyond the registration fee,

23:01.381 --> 23:02.680
I've never taken a cent
from shirley.

23:02.682 --> 23:03.981
<i> (chime rings)</i>

23:04.116 --> 23:05.949
If you really wanna know
what we're doing here,

23:06.018 --> 23:07.684
Observe.

23:07.720 --> 23:10.388
- Thank you, but no.
- Hmm.

23:12.425 --> 23:14.024
- (remembering sigh)

23:15.094 --> 23:17.127
Yes.

23:18.064 --> 23:19.596
(birds chirp)

23:20.900 --> 23:23.033
(shawl rustles)

23:24.170 --> 23:28.038
♪♪♪

23:28.074 --> 23:31.708
(grass crunches underfoot)

23:34.313 --> 23:36.247
(birds chirp)

23:36.249 --> 23:41.618
♪♪♪

23:41.654 --> 23:44.455
- I know some of you are still
feeling uncertain

23:44.524 --> 23:46.389
Because of the recent tragedy,

23:46.426 --> 23:49.092
And I want you all to know
that this is still

23:49.162 --> 23:51.328
<i> A very safe place.</i>

23:51.464 --> 23:53.197
<i> So...</i>

23:53.199 --> 23:55.466
Who would like to come up
and share?

23:59.539 --> 24:01.271
<i> Tina?</i>

24:02.308 --> 24:09.213
♪♪♪

24:11.751 --> 24:13.484
Why are you here?

24:14.787 --> 24:18.355
What do you wanna let go of?

24:18.491 --> 24:21.725
- My mom, uh, was...

24:21.761 --> 24:23.960
Really verbally abusive
when I was a kid.

24:25.164 --> 24:26.764
It was brutal.

24:26.766 --> 24:29.099
And I could never say anything
back--

24:29.101 --> 24:30.667
- (harshly) why not?

24:30.703 --> 24:33.304
- Because she would...
Yell more.

24:33.306 --> 24:35.506
<i> I-I-I was afraid</i>
<i> she was gonna beat me.</i>

24:35.575 --> 24:37.475
- Did she ever hit you?

24:37.610 --> 24:40.177
- No...
- Then stop making excuses.

24:40.179 --> 24:41.778
<i> - I'm not.</i>

24:41.848 --> 24:44.215
<i> She squashed my spirit.</i>

24:44.350 --> 24:47.051
Like I could never want
anything for myself.

24:47.186 --> 24:48.919
I was, I was afraid
it would be taken from me

24:49.054 --> 24:51.589
If I, if I spoke up,
if I wanted anything--

24:51.724 --> 24:54.258
- Grow up!
- (tearing up, breathing hard)

24:56.896 --> 24:59.996
Now you're crying.

25:00.032 --> 25:02.500
Stop blaming your mother.

25:02.635 --> 25:04.301
- (crying)

25:04.370 --> 25:05.936
- If you don't get what
you want,

25:06.071 --> 25:07.738
Whose fault is it?

25:07.807 --> 25:09.906
- (sobs) it's mine.

25:09.942 --> 25:12.376
- Okay, stop! Just, just--

25:12.511 --> 25:13.944
What are you...?

25:14.079 --> 25:15.513
You're retraumatizing her!

25:15.648 --> 25:17.347
- If you don't agree
with my methods,

25:17.383 --> 25:18.915
You're free to leave.

25:18.951 --> 25:22.186
<i> In fact, all of you are.</i>

25:22.188 --> 25:25.756
If anyone here still questions
this process,

25:25.758 --> 25:28.759
Please leave.

25:28.761 --> 25:30.394
- Are you okay?

25:30.529 --> 25:32.896
- (blows out her breath)

25:32.932 --> 25:35.665
You're saying... (deep breath)

25:35.701 --> 25:38.769
What you're saying is...

25:38.904 --> 25:41.839
I'm not that little girl...
(breath hitches)

25:41.841 --> 25:43.873
And my mother can't hurt me.

25:45.745 --> 25:48.345
That it's... It's my life.

25:50.049 --> 25:51.615
(yelling) it's my life!

25:52.685 --> 25:54.718
(laughing) it's my life.

25:55.855 --> 25:58.722
All: (clapping and cheering)

26:02.795 --> 26:04.461
Tina: (exhilarated exhale)

26:04.597 --> 26:05.996
- Here.

26:06.065 --> 26:07.798
Yeah.

26:07.800 --> 26:09.533
Now, listen.

26:09.535 --> 26:11.669
We're gonna be friends,
all right?

26:11.804 --> 26:15.005
Just you and me.
We're--

26:15.074 --> 26:17.608
Oh, hi.

26:17.677 --> 26:19.309
Hmm?

26:21.681 --> 26:23.881
- Brush her, she likes it.

26:23.883 --> 26:25.548
- Oh yeah?
- Yeah.

26:25.585 --> 26:27.418
- Is this part of my therapy?

26:27.420 --> 26:29.820
- (laughs) not on your life.

26:29.955 --> 26:31.622
I'm only here for the horses.

26:31.757 --> 26:33.557
- Mm.

26:33.559 --> 26:35.759
- You know, they'll let you
choose another horse.

26:37.763 --> 26:39.963
- Yeah, I know, but uh....

26:40.032 --> 26:43.367
I don't wanna give up
on her yet.

26:43.369 --> 26:45.569
- Sometimes it's not
a good fit.

26:45.571 --> 26:47.570
I've seen it happen.

26:47.607 --> 26:50.841
No connection,
it's not working.

26:50.976 --> 26:54.311
Then they changes horses and...

26:54.380 --> 26:55.979
It's better.

26:56.048 --> 26:57.381
- Oh.

26:59.318 --> 27:00.984
- You're almost done here,
right?

27:01.053 --> 27:04.988
- Yeah. Time to start thinking
about what comes next.

27:04.991 --> 27:07.524
- Have you heard from jenny?

27:07.593 --> 27:10.593
- Uh, no. She never answered
my letter.

27:12.665 --> 27:14.931
- You know, we could use
an extra hand around here.

27:16.869 --> 27:19.536
Would you consider staying on
as staff?

27:19.605 --> 27:21.271
- (snorts softly)

27:21.407 --> 27:22.940
Yeah, sure.

27:23.075 --> 27:24.708
Well, I'll, I'll think
about it.

27:26.178 --> 27:28.112
(r&b music plays quietly)

27:28.247 --> 27:35.152
♪♪♪

27:37.657 --> 27:38.955
<i> Malik: Mac, look.</i>

27:38.991 --> 27:41.491
(hard tap)
I found it on bunz.

27:43.329 --> 27:45.229
Bunz. It's like, uh,
kijiji for hipsters -

27:45.231 --> 27:47.164
You trade and shop
with people online.

27:47.166 --> 27:48.966
Some guy found it in
a dumpster one block away

27:49.101 --> 27:50.633
From randy smith's house.

27:50.670 --> 27:52.436
- Nice work.
- Thank you.

27:52.438 --> 27:54.004
And hey, I'm gonna find out
about your Thursday thing,

27:54.006 --> 27:57.107
You know.

27:57.109 --> 27:58.709
- Waxing.
- Oh.

27:58.844 --> 28:02.045
- It's my waxing appointment.
- Okay, cool.

28:02.048 --> 28:03.781
Deflect. Yes, that's fine.
- (taps key)

28:03.783 --> 28:05.582
- Huh.

28:05.651 --> 28:06.750
- There's our guy andrew.

28:07.987 --> 28:10.454
<i> - And there's randy.</i>
<i> Randy: Where's your mask?!</i>

28:10.456 --> 28:11.722
Andrew: You-you-you're food
is there.

28:11.791 --> 28:13.990
- Yeah, I seen the food.

28:13.992 --> 28:15.759
Wh-where's your mask?!
- Leave me alone!

28:15.795 --> 28:17.728
- You filthy people
and your viruses!

28:17.797 --> 28:20.130
- Hey, hey! Easy...
Donovan: And there's our knife.

28:20.265 --> 28:23.133
<i> Malik: Hmm. And there's</i>
<i> our defensive wounds.</i>

28:23.268 --> 28:25.502
(bike rattles)

28:25.571 --> 28:27.070
<i> Andrew: Help!</i>
<i> (bike clatters)</i>

28:27.073 --> 28:29.072
<i> Randy: Get out of here!</i>
<i> You don't belong here!</i>

28:29.075 --> 28:31.107
<i> Donovan: He ran him</i>
<i> into traffic.</i>

28:33.679 --> 28:35.412
- (sighs heavily)

28:35.414 --> 28:37.414
(indistinct chatter)

28:37.416 --> 28:38.882
(leaves rustle with each sweep)

28:42.221 --> 28:45.555
(low hum of chatter)

28:48.894 --> 28:50.894
(fire crackles)

28:55.835 --> 28:57.534
<i> (indistinct chatter)</i>

29:00.706 --> 29:02.039
- Hey.
- Hey.

29:02.174 --> 29:03.841
- Hi. Uh, quick question.
- Mm.

29:03.843 --> 29:07.177
- What, uh, is your official
policy on cell phones?

29:07.312 --> 29:09.379
- No phones. Faye says
interference from outside

29:09.515 --> 29:11.681
Can make your "bloom" wither.

29:11.717 --> 29:13.149
- Ah! Okay.

29:13.185 --> 29:16.620
Uh... Oh, and what was, um,
shirley's room number?

29:16.622 --> 29:19.122
- Uh... Number 11.
- Awesome. Thank you.

29:20.459 --> 29:22.326
(broom sweeps)

29:24.196 --> 29:30.601
♪♪♪

29:30.603 --> 29:32.135
(stairs groan underfoot)

29:32.204 --> 29:34.137
(door creaks open)

29:35.641 --> 29:42.546
♪♪♪

29:42.681 --> 29:49.619
♪♪♪

29:49.655 --> 29:55.158
♪♪♪

29:58.664 --> 30:01.398
- I hope you get this.
The signal here is crap.

30:01.533 --> 30:03.901
<i> Girl, where do I begin!</i>

30:03.903 --> 30:06.637
Okay, first, I'm finally
leaving victor.

30:06.639 --> 30:09.439
I called him today
and told him that it's over.

30:09.475 --> 30:11.842
Nicole, it feels amazing!

30:11.911 --> 30:13.710
I feel like myself again,

30:13.779 --> 30:16.112
And it's not just leaving
victor.

30:16.148 --> 30:17.747
I'm in love!

30:17.783 --> 30:19.483
<i> We talk every night,</i>

30:19.618 --> 30:21.518
<i> And I tell him things</i>
<i> I haven't told anyone.</i>

30:21.587 --> 30:23.186
Uh, and he's gorgeous!

30:23.255 --> 30:24.988
Tall, beautiful eyes,

30:25.024 --> 30:27.257
And I don't even mind
his beard!

30:27.392 --> 30:28.892
<i> Bye!</i>

30:31.663 --> 30:32.996
(door creaks open)

30:34.466 --> 30:37.067
(coyote howls in distance)

30:37.069 --> 30:38.869
(owl hoots nearby)

30:45.744 --> 30:48.612
(nocturnal animal calls)

30:49.815 --> 30:51.615
(footsteps thud)

30:55.754 --> 30:58.187
- (exhales sharply) breathe.

31:00.626 --> 31:02.225
Fareed!

31:02.228 --> 31:09.132
♪♪♪

31:09.268 --> 31:16.239
♪♪♪

31:16.242 --> 31:23.246
♪♪♪

31:23.249 --> 31:26.650
♪♪♪

