(foliage rustles underfoot)

31:29.989 --> 31:36.126
♪♪♪

31:36.261 --> 31:38.795
(ominous music)

31:38.864 --> 31:46.870
♪♪♪

31:46.872 --> 31:53.810
♪♪♪

31:53.879 --> 32:00.884
♪♪♪

32:00.886 --> 32:02.618
(ominous music)

32:03.956 --> 32:05.956
(door creaks open
and thumps against wall)

32:07.660 --> 32:10.760
(foliage rustles underfoot)

32:12.598 --> 32:17.701
♪♪♪

32:17.770 --> 32:20.003
(a branch snaps,
jenny gasps)

32:26.312 --> 32:27.945
- Need some help?

32:28.080 --> 32:29.912
- Oh, hah.

32:29.949 --> 32:31.982
Yeah, actually, I do.
I'm a...

32:32.117 --> 32:34.184
Little lost and the flashlights
on these...

32:34.253 --> 32:36.186
(nervous laugh)

32:36.188 --> 32:38.287
- That's why I always bring
these, just in case.

32:40.525 --> 32:42.793
- Is that uh...

32:42.795 --> 32:44.394
Is that poison ivy?

32:44.529 --> 32:46.596
- Yeah, I stepped in some
in the woods.

32:46.665 --> 32:49.332
- Hmm. And when was that?

32:49.335 --> 32:52.335
- Uh, I got claustrophobic
a couple nights ago and...

32:52.338 --> 32:55.205
Snuck out for a walk,
and a smoke.

32:55.207 --> 32:57.874
- Was shirley with you?

32:58.010 --> 32:59.609
She had poison ivy too.

32:59.611 --> 33:01.077
- 'kay, it's not
what you think.

33:01.146 --> 33:03.279
- Well, what should I think,
fareed?

33:03.349 --> 33:05.615
- 'kay, she followed me
into the woods.

33:05.617 --> 33:07.084
'kay, then she kissed me

33:07.086 --> 33:09.285
And she said that her husband
knew and...

33:09.355 --> 33:12.089
She can't wait
and we should leave that night.

33:13.292 --> 33:15.158
She kept talking about
all these conversations

33:15.160 --> 33:16.993
That we had -
we'd stay up late -

33:16.996 --> 33:19.296
And all the promises
that I made to her.

33:19.431 --> 33:21.198
None of it was true.

33:21.333 --> 33:22.965
- What do you mean?

33:23.002 --> 33:25.168
- I never spoke to shirley
before that night.

33:29.641 --> 33:32.375
<i> (siren wails in the distance)</i>

33:35.180 --> 33:37.080
(bicycle spokes click)

33:40.185 --> 33:42.119
- Ben?
- Hey.

33:42.254 --> 33:44.454
- Hey. I'm detective mcavoy.

33:44.589 --> 33:47.723
Um, I'm sure your dad would
like for you to have this.

33:48.861 --> 33:50.594
- Thanks.
- And just so you know,

33:50.729 --> 33:52.562
We have more than enough
evidence to convict the man

33:52.564 --> 33:54.798
Responsible for his death.

33:54.933 --> 33:58.368
- My dad said he wanted
my old bike back for exercise.

33:58.370 --> 34:00.604
- He didn't tell you
he was delivering food?

34:00.606 --> 34:02.672
- He mentioned that some
of his investments took a hit

34:02.741 --> 34:05.275
During the pandemic, but...

34:05.277 --> 34:08.010
(shocked laugh) he sent me
tuition money last week.

34:10.315 --> 34:12.748
- My guess is he wanted
to protect you,

34:12.785 --> 34:14.084
Let you focus on school.

34:14.219 --> 34:16.419
- Who cares about school?

34:16.422 --> 34:18.889
Some racist killed my dad.
He was 65-years-old.

34:18.891 --> 34:20.624
He should've been retired,
and now he's dead!

34:22.027 --> 34:24.895
65 years for what?

34:24.897 --> 34:26.929
To end up like this guy
on the wall?

34:29.968 --> 34:31.668
Where's the fairness in that?

34:31.737 --> 34:36.239
♪♪♪

34:36.241 --> 34:38.108
(receding footsteps
thud lightly)

34:41.580 --> 34:44.514
- Who were you talking to,
shirley?

34:46.218 --> 34:47.984
(window rattles)

34:49.421 --> 34:52.021
(window rattles)

34:53.658 --> 34:57.593
(low, indistinct humming)

35:01.133 --> 35:05.067
(humming)

35:10.109 --> 35:12.642
(humming gets louder)

35:16.682 --> 35:18.080
- Hello?

35:18.117 --> 35:20.216
(humming stops)

35:21.653 --> 35:24.020
- Uh, it's... It's jenny cooper.

35:24.089 --> 35:26.422
I'm the coroner.

35:26.424 --> 35:28.558
What's your name?

35:30.829 --> 35:34.097
Hello?

35:34.099 --> 35:36.133
<i> Look, I just um...</i>

35:36.268 --> 35:38.501
<i> I just wanna know</i>
<i> what happened.</i>

35:38.570 --> 35:40.203
Okay...

35:42.374 --> 35:44.473
(map rustles)

35:47.512 --> 35:54.584
♪♪♪

35:54.586 --> 35:56.052
(knocking)

35:57.489 --> 35:59.121
(door clicks open)

36:01.793 --> 36:03.693
Oliver?

36:05.797 --> 36:07.664
- (sighs heavily)

36:08.800 --> 36:13.803
♪♪♪

36:13.805 --> 36:15.538
- Tell me how it started.

36:18.010 --> 36:21.143
- One night, I heard her
singing through the vent.

36:22.548 --> 36:24.080
I told her she had
a great voice

36:24.149 --> 36:27.284
And it kinda just kept going
from there.

36:28.554 --> 36:32.689
<i> (shirley humming)</i>

36:35.627 --> 36:38.428
♪♪♪

36:38.497 --> 36:41.797
- ♪ it is well ♪

36:44.503 --> 36:47.803
♪ with my soul ♪

36:50.209 --> 36:52.275
♪ it is well ♪

36:53.378 --> 36:56.246
♪ it is well with... ♪

36:57.516 --> 36:59.949
♪ my soul ♪

37:03.588 --> 37:07.090
<i>- It's really cool how you sing</i>
<i> to yourself every night.</i>

37:07.225 --> 37:09.392
- After hard days
it picks me up.

37:12.231 --> 37:14.130
Do you ever feel like...

37:14.132 --> 37:17.734
You're defined by someone
else's idea of you?

37:17.803 --> 37:19.335
<i> - What do you mean?</i>

37:21.073 --> 37:24.541
- Like the one person who's
supposed to love you the most

37:24.543 --> 37:27.543
Has no idea who you really are.

37:27.613 --> 37:31.481
- Yeah. I know exactly
what that's like.

37:33.652 --> 37:35.551
- (laughs) you know,

37:35.553 --> 37:37.354
Let's forget this pity party.

37:37.356 --> 37:39.822
Um, if you could be anywhere
right now,

37:39.891 --> 37:41.358
Where would it be?

37:41.360 --> 37:44.894
<i> Um... First place that comes</i>
<i> to mind.</i>

37:44.963 --> 37:46.896
- The beach.

37:46.965 --> 37:49.065
- I've always wanted to go
to hawaii!

37:49.134 --> 37:51.167
- We should go
and learn how to surf.

37:51.236 --> 37:54.437
- And only have drinks
with umbrellas. (laughs)

37:54.439 --> 37:56.306
- That'd be great.

37:59.511 --> 38:01.477
- Tell me who you are.

38:03.515 --> 38:05.981
- Um...

38:06.018 --> 38:08.318
You'll know me when you see me.

38:08.387 --> 38:10.820
- (snorts softly)

38:10.955 --> 38:12.855
(sighs)

38:15.827 --> 38:18.461
- We would have mellow
conversations, at first.

38:20.298 --> 38:22.699
- And then it turned
into something more?

38:22.701 --> 38:24.934
- It just got too personal.

38:29.074 --> 38:30.940
- I can't talk about it.

38:31.076 --> 38:32.342
<i> - Come on, shirley.</i>

38:32.477 --> 38:35.745
<i> You know you can tell me</i>
<i> anything.</i>

38:35.880 --> 38:39.148
- I've... Never had an orgasm.

38:39.184 --> 38:41.751
- You mean your husband never...
- Never.

38:43.188 --> 38:44.687
- Did you ever talk to him
about it?

38:44.690 --> 38:47.624
- I tried,
and then he tried, but...

38:47.759 --> 38:50.093
It didn't happen.

38:50.095 --> 38:52.929
Then he shut down,
I shut down,

38:53.064 --> 38:55.999
<i> And after, we pretended</i>
<i> everything was fine.</i>

38:56.134 --> 38:58.168
That's what he would
always say, we're fine.

38:58.170 --> 38:59.635
(small laugh)

38:59.637 --> 39:02.372
But I want more than fine,
dammit!

39:04.676 --> 39:07.577
(weeping) I want more
than fine.

39:10.649 --> 39:13.316
God, (chuckles)
would you listen to me.

39:13.318 --> 39:15.118
Faye was right, I'm pathetic.

39:15.187 --> 39:16.986
<i> - No, don't listen to faye.</i>

39:17.055 --> 39:19.088
That's her thing,
to break you down,

39:19.091 --> 39:21.190
Make you feel small.

39:21.226 --> 39:24.260
Shirley, you are not small.
You're immense.

39:24.329 --> 39:26.328
Immensely wonderful,
and smart,

39:26.365 --> 39:28.598
And hilarious, and fun.
- Stop. Please.

39:28.667 --> 39:30.800
- No, no, no, it's true.

39:30.802 --> 39:32.702
You're the best thing
about this whole place

39:32.704 --> 39:35.204
<i> And I can tell that</i>
<i> through a stupid vent.</i>

39:35.240 --> 39:38.408
- It's just,
I've been so lonely...

39:39.945 --> 39:41.678
For years.

39:41.813 --> 39:44.414
(sharp exhales)
sometimes it's so heavy

39:46.485 --> 39:48.684
I can't even get out of bed
in the morning.

39:50.188 --> 39:51.954
<i> I feel like I have no one.</i>

39:53.358 --> 39:55.024
- You have me.

39:56.261 --> 39:57.893
(happy exhale)

39:59.231 --> 40:02.165
- Yeah... I do.

40:06.838 --> 40:10.640
<i> - I knew it had gone too far,</i>
<i> but by then it was too late.</i>

40:10.709 --> 40:12.442
- Gah! (scratching)

40:12.511 --> 40:15.445
Please don't do this!
Don't push me away, fareed.

40:15.447 --> 40:18.047
- What?
What're you talking about?

40:18.049 --> 40:20.183
- I'm sorry I followed you
into the woods--

40:20.185 --> 40:23.352
- Oh no... Shirley,
what did you do?

40:23.388 --> 40:26.021
- I know you're scared,
and you have a lot to lose.

40:26.057 --> 40:28.725
I do too.
But, but I already told victor.

40:28.860 --> 40:30.593
<i> I already got the money.</i>

40:30.662 --> 40:32.662
It's time for
our new beginning.

40:35.233 --> 40:38.601
- I... I don't think
I can do this.

40:38.603 --> 40:41.671
- (breath hitches) what?

40:41.740 --> 40:44.807
- I can't! I can't do this
anymore, shirley!

40:44.876 --> 40:47.343
I can't!

40:47.345 --> 40:50.013
- I blew up my whole life
for you!

40:50.148 --> 40:51.614
(sobbing)

40:53.618 --> 40:56.486
<i> (humming)</i>

40:56.621 --> 41:00.289
♪♪♪

41:01.359 --> 41:03.759
- I didn't mean for shirley
to hurt herself.

41:03.829 --> 41:07.129
It wasn't supposed to be real.

41:07.199 --> 41:08.965
- Well, it was real
for shirley.

41:10.068 --> 41:11.968
- (sighs heavily)

41:16.775 --> 41:19.408
L bounces,
chain net rattles)

41:21.045 --> 41:23.178
(horns honk in the distance)

41:25.784 --> 41:29.852
- Hey, pop!
- Hey!

41:29.921 --> 41:31.854
Twice in one week.
What's...

41:31.923 --> 41:34.524
What's going on?

41:34.593 --> 41:36.259
What?

41:37.596 --> 41:39.596
What's this?
- For your trip.

41:39.731 --> 41:42.065
There's another one
in there for mindy.

41:42.200 --> 41:43.800
- So all of a sudden,
you don't have a problem

41:43.935 --> 41:45.401
With my vacation?

41:45.470 --> 41:47.737
- I don't wanna be the one that
stops you from shining, pops.

41:47.739 --> 41:50.873
- All right! (laughs)

41:50.876 --> 41:52.074
- Ungh!

41:52.143 --> 41:54.343
♪ every now and then ♪

41:55.747 --> 41:58.247
♪ makes no difference ♪

41:58.283 --> 42:02.218
♪ where you're going ♪

42:02.220 --> 42:04.687
♪ you may be feeling low ♪

42:04.723 --> 42:08.824
♪ oh, but let your face glow ♪

42:08.826 --> 42:11.427
♪ your smile is so easy ♪
(camera whirs)

42:11.496 --> 42:15.431
♪ and it comes naturally ♪

42:15.500 --> 42:17.833
♪ you must remember ♪

42:17.869 --> 42:21.838
♪ yeah, through the rain ♪
(machine buzzes)

42:21.840 --> 42:24.774
♪ there'll be sunshine again ♪

42:24.909 --> 42:31.847
♪♪♪

42:31.883 --> 42:39.989
♪♪♪

42:39.991 --> 42:42.291
(text message chimes)

42:44.896 --> 42:51.067
♪♪♪

42:51.136 --> 42:54.070
♪ so try a little smile ♪

42:54.072 --> 42:56.339
♪ every now and then ♪

42:56.341 --> 42:57.973
- Who is it?

42:59.444 --> 43:00.643
- It's jenny.

43:00.778 --> 43:04.414
♪ treat your face the best ♪

43:04.416 --> 43:06.616
♪ you must remember ♪

43:06.685 --> 43:10.486
♪ yeah, through the rain ♪
(phone thumps on table)

43:10.555 --> 43:12.155
♪♪♪

43:12.290 --> 43:13.656
(exhales nervously)

43:16.494 --> 43:18.027
♪ so try a new smile ♪

43:18.162 --> 43:19.161
♪♪♪

43:22.400 --> 43:24.767
♪ every now and then ♪

